President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Michael A. Khouri for the position of Commissioner of the Federal Maritime Commission. Khouri has been a Commissioner on the Federal Maritime Commission since 2010 and has 45 years of experience in the maritime industry. He has worked at the law firm of Pedley & Gordinier and held executive positions at MERS/Economy Boat and American Commercial Lines. Khouri began his career in the marine industry in 1971 and has served on the Board of Directors of the American Waterways Operators Association and the Waterways Council, Inc. He holds a B.A. from Tulane University and a J.D. from the Brandeis School of Law at the University of Louisville.